article.description: Trevor Knight threw for four touchdowns as New Hampshire rolled to a 40-17 win over Towson on Saturday.
article.headline: Knight with 4 TDs, New Hampshire rolls over Towson 40-17
article.linkText: Knight with 4 TDs, New Hampshire rolls over Towson 40-17
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Trevor Knight threw for four touchdowns as New Hampshire rolled to a 40-17 win over Towson on Saturday. Knight was 19-for-30 for 197 yards passing for the Wildcats (5-2, 3-1 Colonial Athletic Conference). DeUnte Chatman ran for 187 yards and two scores and Brandon Gallagher added 104 rushing yards. Overall, New Hampshire outgained Towson 508-279. Chatman ran for a 26-yard score in the first quarter and Knight followed with four unanswered touchdown passes in the second -- one each to Kieran Presley and Neil O'Connor and two to Nick Lorden -- for a 33-3 halftime lead. Chatman's second score came early in the third, extending the Wildcats' margin to 40-3. Kanyia Anderson scored for Towson on a 93-yard fumble recovery return early in the fourth quarter and Ryan Stover threw a touchdown pass with 4:32 to play for the final score. Stover finished with 194 yards passing for the Tigers (2-5, 0-4). --- More AP college football: http://www.collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
